def: A lower conduit; a subterranean conduit. [Obs.] Sir H. Wotton.
Bearing a horn, or horns, on the nose, as the rhinoceros.
To rot, as flax or hemp, by exposure to rain, dew, and sun. SeeDewretting.
Filth; abomination. [Obs.]To purge the snottery of our slimy time. Marston.
To void the excrement, as a bird; to mute. [Obs.]
A record of what passes in the night; a nightly journal; --distinguished from diary. [R.] Addison.
A house where ale is retailed; hence, a tippling house.Macaulay.
As much as a tumbler will hold; enough to fill a tumbler.
